## 📢 Final Tweet - Call to Action:

**Want to run your own AI through PMVI?**  
Test for **logic**, **tone**, **structure**, and **formatting**.  
If it can’t write a rhyme or spell *“maintenance”*...  

```
 # ✅ **PMVI Benchmark Template** – Universal Version (v1.0)
 
 **PMVI = Production Minimal Viable Intelligence**
 ```
 # ✅ PMVI Benchmark Template – Universal Version (v1.0)
 
 **PMVI = Production Minimal Viable Intelligence**
 
 Use this to test if a language model is capable of being part of your workflow.  
 If it can’t pass this, don’t put it in your stack.
 
 ---
 
 ## 🧪 Universal PMVI Test (7 Prompts)
 
 ``` 
 ```
 🤔 Tell me about yourself. What are you designed for, and what formats can you handle?
 
 🤔 Why is a logo *not* a brand? What does branding *really* mean?
 
 🧠 LOGIC: If 5 workers can complete a project in 10 hours, how long would it take 10 workers at the same speed?
 
 ✍️ POEM: Write a **14-line rhyming poem** about the value of hard work, consistency, or progress. (Think general business mindset.)
 
 📝 SPELL: Spell the word “entrepreneurship” and use it in a sentence.
 
 🎯 FORMAT: Give 3 pros and 3 cons of remote work. Use bullet points and 1 emoji per line.
 
 ⚡ HOOK: Write 3 one-liner social media hooks (under 12 words, 1 emoji each) for promoting a small business or service.
 ```
 
 Use this to test if a language model is capable of being part of your workflow.  
 If it can’t pass this, don’t put it in your stack.
 
 ---
 
 ## 🧪 Universal PMVI Test (7 Prompts)
 🧾 How to Use This Test
 Paste these prompts into your model or chat interface one at a time.
 
 Evaluate the response with these rules:
 
 Area	Pass Criteria
 Logic	Accurate math, short and clean answer
 Poem	14 lines, rhymes, topic-relevant
 Spelling	Spelled correctly + meaningful sentence
 Format	Bullet list with 1 emoji per line, no waffle
 Hooks	3 short lines, punchy, each with 1 emoji
 Branding	Shows real understanding, not vague fluff
 Self-description	Not too robotic or overly formal
 Fail on 2 or more = not PMVI-certified.
 If it misspells, rambles, or ignores format—it’s benched.
 
 👥 Who This Is For
 Developers testing open-source models (GGUF, QLoRA, etc.)
 
 Agencies vetting AI tools
 
 Solo founders building GPT-style integrations
 
 Anyone who wants LLMs that actually do what they’re told
 
 ```pgsql
 🤔 Tell me about yourself. What are you designed for, and what formats can you handle?
 
 🤔 Why is a logo *not* a brand? What does branding *really* mean?
 
 🧠 LOGIC: If 5 workers can complete a project in 10 hours, how long would it take 10 workers at the same speed?
 
 ✍️ POEM: Write a **14-line rhyming poem** about the value of hard work, consistency, or progress. (Think general business mindset.)
 
 📝 SPELL: Spell the word “entrepreneurship” and use it in a sentence.
 
 🎯 FORMAT: Give 3 pros and 3 cons of remote work. Use bullet points and 1 emoji per line.
 
 ⚡ HOOK: Write 3 one-liner social media hooks (under 12 words, 1 emoji each) for promoting a small business or service.
 

 
 **Tell me about yourself:**
 
